---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Projects | contextself"
  description="Side projects exploring ideas about equilibrium and balance"
>
  <div class="projects">
    <h1>Projects</h1>
    <p class="intro">
      Occasionally, ideas want to become something more concrete.
    </p>

    <article class="project">
      <h2>
        <a href="https://github.com/daidaitaotao/taocore" target="_blank">TaoCore</a>
      </h2>
      <p>
        An attempt to take equilibrium thinking seriously in software.
        Instead of asking "what's optimal?", it asks "what's stable?"
        Instead of maximizing, it watches for convergence.
      </p>
      <p>
        It grew out of frustration with arbitrary stopping conditions in
        iterative systems—<code>for i in range(10)</code> feels like giving up.
        What if the system could recognize when it had found balance?
      </p>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="https://github.com/daidaitaotao/taocore" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://pypi.org/project/taocore/" target="_blank">PyPI</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="project">
      <h2>
        <a href="https://github.com/daidaitaotao/taocore-human" target="_blank">TaoCore Human</a>
      </h2>
      <p>
        A domain layer on top of TaoCore for processing images and videos
        into behavioral signals. It extracts what can be observed—faces,
        poses, proximity, co-occurrence—without claiming to know what
        people are thinking or feeling.
      </p>
      <p>
        The system is designed around uncertainty: every signal carries
        confidence, non-convergence means ambiguity, and refusal is built in.
        It asks "what patterns are stable?" not "what is this person like?"
      </p>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="https://github.com/daidaitaotao/taocore-human" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
        <a href="https://pypi.org/project/taocore-human/" target="_blank">PyPI</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .projects {
    max-width: 65ch;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .intro {
    color: #7f8c8d;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .project {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .project h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .project h2 a {
    color: #2c3e50;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .project h2 a:hover {
    color: #3498db;
  }

  .project p {
    color: #5d6d7e;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .project code {
    font-family: 'SF Mono', 'Monaco', 'Inconsolata', 'Fira Mono', monospace;
    background: #f4f5f7;
    padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem;
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.9em;
    color: #2c3e50;
  }

  .links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .links a {
    color: #7f8c8d;
    text-decoration: none;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .links a:hover {
    color: #3498db;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
    }

    .project h2 {
      font-size: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
